LEXSense.DefinitionShort: particle linking an event to a point in space; = relation indicating that event X ends at point in space Y
particle linking an event to a point in time; = relation indicating that event X ends at point in time Y
particle linking two events; = relation indicating that event X ends at the time of occurrence or completion of event Y
particle linking an event to an object; = relation indicating that the main argument of event X is comparable to object Y
particle linking two objects, of which the first is not always listed explicitly; = relation indicating that object X and object Y are at opposite ends of a range of similar objects
particle linking an event to an object; = relation indicating that event X results in the existence of object Y
particle linking an event to an object; = relation indicating that event X results in a certain level of status for object Y
= process by which an event gradually increases in intensity
= state in which an event takes place with a strong intensity
literally: until death; hence: = state in which a certain emotion is felt with an extreme intensity
= state in which a certain event is performed with joy
= state in which a group of objects is high in quantity
particle linking two events; = relation indicating that event X and event Y are at opposite ends of a range of similar events
particle linking an event to a participant; = relation indicating that event X is focused on object Y
particle marking a phrase indicating that an event is taking place with a certain frequency; = marker emphasizing the high frequence of an event
particle marking a phrase indicating that an event is taking place at a relatively fast speed; = marker emphasizing the relatively high speed of an event
particle marking a phrase indicating a certain quantity; = marker emphasizing that the quantity expressed will not be exceeded
literally: up to one; particle marking a phrase indicating a certain quantity; = marker emphasizing that not even the quantity expressed has been reached
